BackEnd

Class FloorTile

  • java.lang.Object
    • BackEnd.Tile
      • BackEnd.FloorTile

  • public class FloorTile
extends Tile
    The FloorTile class will be the floor tiles of the Game board. These will hold information about the floor tile such as the tile type, if the tile is on fire and the rotaion of the tile.
    Author:
    Atif Ishaq & Joshua Oladitan

      • setFireTic

        public void setFireTic(int numOfPlayers)
        This method sets the boolean onFire to true, which means the tile is now on fire also ticks down until two player cycles has happened. isOnFire is then set to false as the fire has worn out.
        Parameters:
        numOfPlayers - This lets us know how many ticks are in one cycle. Each player is one tick.

      • ticFire

        public void ticFire()
        This method decrements the ticFire after every players turn. If it reaches zero, sets isOnFire to false.

      • setFrozenTic
